# Elementor Module Structure

Every module lives in its own self-contained folder. No exceptions.

## Directory Layout

```
modules/
  module-name/
    widget-module-name.php   # Elementor widget class
    module-name.js           # Front-end JavaScript (enqueued only when widget is on page)
    module-name.css          # Front-end styles (enqueued only when widget is on page)
```

- Folder and file names: **lowercase, hyphenated** (`hero-banner`, `pricing-table`)
- Widget PHP file prefix: `widget-` (e.g. `widget-hero-banner.php`)
- One widget class per file; class name: `TRS_Widget_Hero_Banner` (prefix `TRS_Widget_`)

## Widget PHP Skeleton

```php
<?php
if ( ! defined( 'ABSPATH' ) ) exit;

class TRS_Widget_Module_Name extends \Elementor\Widget_Base {

    public function get_name(): string        { return 'trs-module-name'; }
    public function get_title(): string       { return esc_html__( 'Module Name', 'trs-kit' ); }
    public function get_icon(): string        { return 'eicon-plug'; }
    public function get_categories(): array   { return [ 'trs-kit' ]; }

    public function get_style_depends(): array  { return [ 'trs-module-name' ]; }
    public function get_script_depends(): array { return [ 'trs-module-name' ]; }

    protected function register_controls(): void { /* controls here */ }
    protected function render(): void            { /* template here */ }
}
```

## Asset Registration

Register and enqueue assets in the **main plugin/kit loader**, not inside the widget class:

```php
wp_register_style(
    'trs-module-name',
    TRS_KIT_URL . 'modules/module-name/module-name.css',
    [],
    TRS_KIT_VERSION
);

wp_register_script(
    'trs-module-name',
    TRS_KIT_URL . 'modules/module-name/module-name.js',
    [ 'jquery' ],
    TRS_KIT_VERSION,
    true
);
```

Assets are loaded on demand via `get_style_depends()` / `get_script_depends()` — Elementor handles conditional loading automatically.

## Widget Registration

```php
\Elementor\Plugin::instance()->widgets_manager->register( new TRS_Widget_Module_Name() );
```

Call this on `elementor/widgets/register` action hook.
